The Romanian utility Cia de Apa
Oltenia SA awarded a 39 million-lei ($11 million) contract for
water-treatment plant upgrades in the south of the country to
local construction company Coral SRL.  The contract, initially estimated at 41.5 million lei,
includes water-treatment plant works in the town of Calafat,
according to  a notice  published today on the European Unionâ€™s
tender website. The utility had received a total of eight bids
for the contract, according to the notice.  To contact the reporter on this story:
